Date: Fri, 6 Mar 2015 17:23:19 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 241/441] xhci: Workaround for PME stuck issues in Intel xhci

The xhci in Intel Sunrisepoint and Cherryview platforms need a driver
workaround for a Stuck PME that might either block PME events in suspend,
or create spurious PME events preventing runtime suspend.

Workaround is to clear a internal PME flag, BIT(28) in a vendor specific
PMCTRL register at offset 0x80a4, in both suspend resume callbacks

Without this, xhci connected usb devices might never be able to wake up the
system from suspend, or prevent device from going to suspend (xhci d3)

Cc: <stable@vger.kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Mathias Nyman <mathias.nyman@linux.intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>
Backported-by: Wade Cline <wade.t.cline@intel.com>
---
 drivers/usb/host/xhci-pci.c | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/usb/host/xhci-pci.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/host/xhci-pci.c
@@ -39,6 +39,7 @@
 #define PCI_DEVICE_ID_INTEL_LYNXPOINT_XHCI	0x8c31
 #define PCI_DEVICE_ID_INTEL_LYNXPOINT_LP_XHCI	0x9c31
 #define PCI_DEVICE_ID_INTEL_CHERRYVIEW_XHCI		0x22b5
+(??)
 #define PCI_DEVICE_ID_INTEL_SUNRISEPOINT_H_XHCI		0xa12f
 #define PCI_DEVICE_ID_INTEL_SUNRISEPOINT_LP_XHCI	0x9d2f
 
@@ -143,6 +144,7 @@ static void xhci_pci_quirks(struct devic
 	if (pdev->vendor == PCI_VENDOR_ID_INTEL &&
 		(pdev->device == PCI_DEVICE_ID_INTEL_SUNRISEPOINT_LP_XHCI ||
 		 pdev->device == PCI_DEVICE_ID_INTEL_SUNRISEPOINT_H_XHCI ||
+		 pdev->device == PCI_DEVICE_ID_INTEL_PUMA7_XHCI ||
 		 pdev->device == PCI_DEVICE_ID_INTEL_CHERRYVIEW_XHCI)) {
 		xhci->quirks |= XHCI_PME_STUCK_QUIRK;
 	}
@@ -303,6 +305,9 @@ static int xhci_pci_suspend(struct usb_h
 
 	if (xhci->quirks & XHCI_PME_STUCK_QUIRK)
 		xhci_pme_quirk(xhci);
+
+	if (xhci->quirks & XHCI_PME_STUCK_QUIRK)
+		xhci_pme_quirk(xhci);
 
 	return xhci_suspend(xhci, do_wakeup);
 }
